text: Okay I have a few more problems with where this movie is going:  1) The plot is becoming convoluted. It's gone from "the island is exploding and we need to evacuate it, also let's find Blue" to "also there's this evil corporation trying to do ...something... a la InGen in TLW:JP, and apparently they've engineered a new raptor-rex terror hybrid like in the last film." An action-adventure film with a convoluted plot is hard to follow and kinda off-putting. 2) This is starting to feel same-y. Not only do they have the corporate plan element from The Lost World and the hybrid from JW, but visually it's also very similar to the last film ‚Äì right down to featuring that hamster wheel thing again. 3) The Marvel humour is creeping in. Somehow I don't think that's gonna fit the tone of a film called "Fallen Kingdom" but by all means. 4) It bears repeating that the dinosaurs in the original film weren't monsters, just animals. You could get away with the monster element with the I-rex in JW because it was sort of a failed genetic experiment, and that was like the point of the film, but here the focus is on the island exploding and yet you're bringing the horror element back anyway. It just kinda feels cheap and out of place here.  I know I'm probably complaining a bit too much about a film that I have no intention of seeing in theatres, but I feel invested nonetheless because of my affinity for the original film and by extension its IP which you are using here. If this were a no-name original property I wouldn't care to express my opinion, but when you use the Jurassic name to increase your box office draw, just know that you will be hearing from the likes of me.
author: Matt William

text: Ok, I've seen a lot of people messing up the dinosaurs in the movie, specifically 2. The Indoraptor, which is in the house scene, is different than the baryonyx, which is in the pipe scene with the fire/lava, and for those that say it looks a little like a spinosaurus, the 2 are genetically related, like how dogs are very similar and share many attributes, but are also very different. Baryonyx is a real dino, and the indoraptor is a hybid that is similar to the indominus rex. My assumption is that the Indoraptor has the base Genome of a velociraptor, while the indominus rex, as stated in the first jurassic world, has the base genome of a tyranosauraus Rex, aka T-Rex. The Indoraptor may have other mutations and/or features specifically added to its dna from other things, but we are not sure yet.

text: God this looks like a steaming pile of shit. It definitely looks, just from the trailer, better than Jurassic world 1 was. But that's not a very high bar. I mean seriously, there's nothing good about these. Too many ex machinas, too many plot holes that will be inexplicable except by fans that need to explain it so they don't feel as bad about liking the movie, too much in your face exposition, and for God sake, just get rid of the hybrid dinosaurs. They're not necessary at all. They're just a lazy story-teller's tool. "Oh I can't think of a way for a T-Rex to be more exciting, like writing a better story, so let's cut the better story out and just make a hybrid dinosaur". Your movies have no impact, they're forgettable except the title, and the characters are so 1 dimensional, it's disgusting. After the last 3 movies (jp3, jw, jw2), you might as well take the entire Jurassic Park franchise out back and put it out of its misery.

text: I love Jurassic Park, Jurassic World, and prehistoric life. But my peers and family members say that it is not appropriate for my age, is immature, childish, not productive, is the reason why I‚Äôm friendzoned by girls, is making me behind kids my age group, and is the reason why I am so out of this world and why I am ‚Äúdetached from reality.‚Äù I put that in parenthesis because I do not believe that I am detached from reality. I believe that I‚Äôm just being myself. There was this dude recently in high school who told me that if I want a gf, I have to be a real man by getting my mind off those things, play sports, instead of being a beta male Asian with quirky interests. I posts pictures on Instagram of my artwork on prehistoric animals in their respective time periods and Ive also done artworks on early dogs, giraffes, horses and whales. But many of my friends unfollowed me. I asked them why and they said its because Instagram is not for posting artwork. They said its more for posting college pictures and pictures of your friends. And they told me that those artworks did not make them feel like they could relate to my life anymore so they unfollowed me. And they suggested to me that I should quit Instagram because Instagram is not for me. My aunt makes false accusations out of me to her friends and says that I post my artworks on social media just to impress people, get their approval, and that I‚Äôm an attention seeker. I can assure you none of that about me is true! I was really hurt of what happened and it is still taking me a while to recover. I asked myself if I‚Äôm weird and less interesting. And I felt as if my heart was smashed by a big hammer and I felt as if I‚Äôm not accepted by the social circle of society. I considered those friends who unfollowed me to be really good friends. Some of them I knew since grade school. But I guess they changed a lot. It hurts especially when your own family members are doing this to you when they are suppose to be in support of you and love you for who you are.

text: Seems like we finally got a Jurassic Park film where tons of dinosaurs run rampant in the streets. I know Jurassic Park 2 had just the T-Rex, but that was just it, and it didnt go on *that* much of a rampage.  But now that I think about, our weapons would be able to take them out pretty fast. At best, T-Rexes and Triceritops would put up a long fight. That being said, these custom made dinos, they'd probably adapt to modern weapons, if these pricks keep making them.  In hindsight, I can see cloning regilar dinos in the Jurassic Park universe making sense, you're tampering with anything(except the gender, last I recall). But combinging DNA and traits, making brand new creatures, you're just *begging* for a damn Kaiju attack to happen one of these days.  Oh shit, and Legendary are working on this. If this results in a new Kaiju for its own Kaiju movie, or future Godzilla, King Kong, or Pacific Rim movie, I'm in.

text: Jurassic World: Fallen Kingdom is an upcoming American science fiction adventure film directed by J. A. Bayona. The film is a sequel to Jurassic World (2015) and is the fifth installment of the Jurassic Park film series, as well as the second installment of a planned Jurassic World trilogy. The film features Derek Connolly and Jurassic World director Colin Trevorrow both returning as writers, with Trevorrow and original Jurassic Park director Steven Spielberg acting as executive producers. The film is set on the fictional island of Isla Nublar, located off Central America's Pacific Coast. Filming took place from February to July 2017 in England and Hawaii.  Chris Pratt, Bryce Dallas Howard, and B. D. Wong will reprise their roles from the previous film, with James Cromwell, Ted Levine, Justice Smith, Geraldine Chaplin, Daniella Pineda, Toby Jones, Rafe Spall, and Isabella Sermon joining the cast. Jeff Goldblum will reprise his role as Dr. Ian Malcolm from the original film and its 1997 sequel.  Universal Pictures has scheduled the film to be released in the United Kingdom on June 7, 2018, and the United States on June 22, 2018.

VS The Simpsons writers working with this new canon and to establish this as the truth of what actually happened. Hopefully the original creators will see the demand and make this official.  Perhaps even pay us because we are fixing their mistakes. If you wish to join my new canon, feel free to write your own story but you must submit it to me for approval. You can use my email ;   theRealSesame Street VS Spider-Man MEETS Super Mario Bros. VS The Simpsonswriter@gattormail.com You can also send constructive reviews there, but no petty criticisms. If I get motivations muddled,its because my cat distracted me.  Also, if you don't like my story you don't have to have read it. Unstopable Serenity Darkmoon Raven got out of the shower and put some clothes onher hot steaming naked body.She wore a dress the same color as her eyes her father brought her from the city. After she was no longer naked, they left to defeat Green Goblin.  Along the way they summoned Harry, who joined them on their quest.  "I will join you on your quest to defeat Green Goblin said Harry Osborn.  "Thanks for joining us on our quest," said Mario; "Yes, we need your help to defeat Green Goblin" said Unstopable Serenity Darkmoon Raven. So, Unstopable Serenity Darkmoon Raven Mario and now Unstopable Serenity Darkmoon Raven left by terrain wagon for their epic quest to defeat the prince of all uglyness ...... Norman Osborn!  Over the next few days, more and more horrific reports came from the direction of Norman Osborn's hanger.  First it was just the criminals being arrested and put to work in Green Goblin's armies. Then anyone who was against Green Goblin was also arrested and put to trial. They were separated into groups of men and women. The men were put to work, the women were rapped until killed. "????!!" questioned Mario exclaimingly. Because in the doorway, no other than Norman Osborn stood! And lightning struck int he background and showed villain as a silluette. "Indeed, that is the only logical explanation," said Super Mario, who of course had thought of it before Harry did but was too noble and modest to say so.     "Well, I say we kill him now." said Toadsworth. "That is a good idea," said Mario and he reached for his howdah pistol.  But then all the sudden, they were surrounded! As ever as revoking as it always had been.  If only Mario could get to it! Then Mario remembered... He had the power of go karting!  Before Green Goblin could turn to the loyal followers, Mario lept forward and grabbed the The Letter E from mercenarys's hands. Mario then apologised profoundly and patted the loyal followers on their back. "Green Goblin," said Mario, "I'm sorry, but it's better for you never ever to remember who you were." And with Super Mario's Stomping, he crushed the The Letter E. "Noooooo!" Norman Osborn said, "Now I will never know who I am!"  "Well, I'm not going to let you get away with all the misery you've caused!" yelled Toadsworth. He grabbed a lazer gun and smashed Green Goblin's head open. text: While this new dino DOES share many similarities to a raptor, it is clearly much bigger than it. I personally believe it to be a baryonyx, a different type of theropod that was capable of swimming long distances, and primarily hunted fish. Think spinosaur, but smaller and not the massive dorsal fin on its back. This type of dinosaur would make sense, considering that the island itself is crumbling due to a volcano, and since its an island obviously surrounded by water, the baryonyx could profit from this type of environment. Especially considering the scene where they fall off the edge into the ocean in one of those gyro-ball things(whatever they called them in the last movie), the baryonyx could easily hunt that kind of thing down.

text: A man is driving down the road and his car breaks down near a monastery. He goes to the monastery, knocks on the door, and says, "My car broke down. Do you think I could stay the night?" The monks graciously accept him, feed him dinner, even fix his car. As the man tries to fall asleep, he hears a strange sound. A sound unlike anything he's ever heard before. The Sirens that nearly seduced Odysseus into crashing his ship comes to his mind. He doesn't sleep that night. He tosses and turns trying to figure out what could possibly be making such a seductive sound. The next morning, he asks the monks what the sound was, but they say, "We can't tell you. You're not a monk." Distraught, the man is forced to leave. Years later, after never being able to forget that sound, the man goes back to the monastery and pleads for the answer again. The monks reply, "We can't tell you. You're not a monk." The man says, "If the only way I can find out what is making that beautiful sound is to become a monk, then please, make me a monk." The monks reply, "You must travel the earth and tell us how many blades of grass there are and the exact number of grains of sand. When you find these answers, you will have become a monk." The man sets about his task. After years of searching he returns as a gray- haired old man and knocks on the door of the monastery. A monk answers. He is taken before a gathering of all the monks. "In my quest to find what makes that beautiful sound, I traveled the earth and have found what you asked for: By design, the world is in a state of perpetual change. Only God knows what you ask. All a man can know is himself, and only then if he is honest and reflective and willing to strip away self deception." The monks reply, "Congratulations. You have become a monk. We shall now show you the way to the mystery of the sacred sound." The monks lead the man to a wooden door, where the head monk says, "The sound is beyond that door." The monks give him the key, and he opens the door. Behind the wooden door is another door made of stone. The man is given the key to the stone door and he opens it, only to find a door made of ruby. And so it went that he needed keys to doors of emerald, pearl and diamond. Finally, they come to a door made of solid gold. The sound has become very clear and definite. The monks say, "This is the last key to the last door." The man is apprehensive to no end. His life's wish is behind that door! With trembling hands, he unlocks the door, turns the knob, and slowly pushes the door open. Falling to his knees, he is utterly amazed to discover the source of that haunting and seductive sound...... ... ... ... ... ... ... ... But, of course, I can't tell you what it is because you're not a monk.

text: Pfff... Please tell me those first shots of a dino and dino hands are work in progress? I CAN'T be the finished shot when it looks more fake than what we got 25 years ago?  Other than that, probably gonna watch it. It's Jurassic after all. Part of my childhood! Although, I'm very much against going down the "man and dino friends"-road. That's imo where the first sequels went wrong. The raptors were some of the best movie baddies ever because they were terrifyingly efficient killers that didn't care much for emotions and empathy. All in all, animals who just wanted to hunt humans. You're undermining their badass-ness when you start making bonds between them and humans and giving them more intelligence for anything other than being ruthless killers. Just my two cents ;)

text: Pretty solid trailer over all. The destruction of the island/s is long overdue  and if this franchise is to grow in any real meaningful way its got to step out of babypen.  Genetically altered dinosaurs have been part of the core foundation of this series so weaponized dinosaurs was another thing we were going to come to eventually. Really while to perfect, the premiss has been handled very well so far  On the subject of saving the dinosaurs (SPOILERS) from what I can find out while it billed as a rescue mission to save them in reality its just so INGEN can sell them off. Likely with the fall of JK and all the lawsuits, they are currently prohibited from cloning new dinosaurs for public use until everything's cleared up. So with no new parks on the horizon they are just out to get back the "property" and profit off of it as best they can. (SPOILERS END)  As for the Indoraptor, I'm baffled by people asking "why make another monster you cannot control?". Well why wouldn't they? The Indominus Rex was nothing but a prototype, an early stage experimental bio-weapon built under the cover a new park attraction. It was never the final product. In fact it's little rampage could be looked as an accidental  "Field Test". It single  handedly brought down Jurassic Kingdom, a facility designed to contain such a creature, displayed incredible abilities and adaptability and to top it off it overcame almost every single human attempt to capture or kill it. If that's not pretty dame good data to show investors  that am more refined and controllable version of such a weapon is worth a buy I don't know what is. Plus with parks and dinosaurs off the table, weapons and hybrids are the future for the company it would seem

text: This movie is look better every time!! :) but really they SHOULD have just called it Jurassic PARK V(5),Jurassic PARK:Fallen Kingdom,Jurassic PARK:Fallen Kingdom/World, or Jurassic PARK:Nublar or Island Falling or SOMETHING to set this apart from Jurassic World in order to further drive home the point that the actually Jurassic World PARK is no more, and the island looks like its been growing over the park's remains,thus making this movie a Jurassic PARK film and NOT World,since the park is now non'-existent   Even more reasoning: Going back to Lost World and Jurassic Park 3(yes I know everyone hates that one but i actually liked it and im including it anyway)....in Lost World,looking at the title it didn't need the Jurassic Park title it could have just used the Lost World title and we would have known it was a JP movie because that's the title of the BOOK. But Spielberg probably felt he needed to further drive home the point that it was a JP movie and sequel. Also in the actual movie Hammond tells Jeff Golblum's character that Island Sorna was "the factory floor" and not meant to be another park island and yet the movie is titled JURASSIC PARK ....even though the only park alluded to in the movie is an opera house that originally planned to be constructed to be the original park but never reached completion....so there you have it,NO park there yet we have the JP title.  Moving on to Jurassic PARK 3: we are brought back to scenic Isla Sorna and it looks like INGEN(or is it NGEN?) has been up to no good constructing their own compound and putting up fences to attempt to contain dinosaurs,but throughout the movie we don't see any evidence supporting INGEN/NGEN having any plans for visitors??? Hmmm what's going on here??  I don't see a park here....more like a dog pound for dinosaurs because a big overreaching company tried to setup their OWN operation on the island and FAILED.....so once again NO park here,and yet again we have the JP title,which only serves to show this is a 2nd but non-book related,sequel  That in mind,why the sequel title Jurassic WORLD when this ACTUAL park is DESTROYED? The ORIGINAL Jurassic Park served to show Hammond's dream of people AACTUALLY coming to a PARK to see live dinosaurs....and Jurassic World is set apart from this movie to show us 20 years later another new,but ACTUAL park got built(and apparently as referenced in the movie actually was just fine for some time) and this park was named Jurassic WORLD thus we get the WORLD title there.   But again,this same park is in RUINS yet still the WORLD title??? We can all understand this is a SEQUEL,but the park is destroyed so why not the PARK title here???  Come on guys!!! Still PLENTY of time to be smart and change the title!!!

text: I get why people think the beginning is scary, but... honestly, it's hard for me to be on edge watching it due to it being the most used cliche in all of the Jurassic movies. Scary music (or none at all, which is usually better) + dino shadows + scared people + dino reveal + slow creeping + scuffle to escape = recipe for a Jurassic cliche. I'm not saying the build up and effects weren't great. It looks well done. I'm simply saying I've been over-exposed to every cliche the Jurassic movies have come out with, so they don't affect me as much. ^^; But we're just here to see dinos, right? :)  Also, have they gone so far as to make Blue a family pet? Seems like it based on the setting. I hope not, because that's just as dumb as trusting a group of raptors won't turn on you just because you trained and raised them. It's the same reason you shouldn't keep wild animals as pets, even if you raised it from birth. They have instincts. They even kill their own kind if they have to. Let them be wild, dammit.

text: Sadly looks terrible. Can we please stop adding indominous to the beginning of every dinosaur , just to try and come up with some crappy storyline and just stick with the original ones. It seems as if they have to put indominous infront of everything because they have turned normal dinosaurs into pets! Blue? seriously yeah mate meet my allogator pink ranger, she's so friendly I reared her from an egg and she always uses her massive jaws to rip apart anyone who tries to mess with me. Seriously, these are prehistoric animals with a prehistoric brain, they definitely would not be tamed, just like you can't tame a flipping crocodile. Speilberg made the raptors scary in jp, and the t-rex scene was awesome. And for anyone who thinks im being a buzz kill, the idea for indominous dino's were just an idea they came up with because it took them years to think of a half decent storyline after they scrapped the idea to give the dinosaurs guns! Come to think of it that may have been better than this crap. Most of us just want big scary normal dino's like from the first film, running wild in the park, causing mayhem, eating tourists, chasing people intertwined with an interesting plot with some suspense, not hybrid dino half crab, half sheep, half cat, half meerkat, that they decide to splice the DNA with. I don't want scary indo dinosaurs I want scary scary dinosaurs. The first jw was weak at best, the visuals were mostly CGI and not even a patch on the visuals from jp over 20 years ago! and they gave the helm to trevorrow who had only done one indie film prior to it. Guaranteed hadcore fans of jp will be disappointed and I think if Crichton were still alive, he would be pissed that his franchise has been butchered. I was really hoping even after the mess of jw, they might be able to turn it around, but I am soooooo dissapointed.

text: I lost a bit of hope with this trailer. the first trailer showed things that I liked. I fear with this trailer that the movie is going to be an action movie about the wildlife enthusiasts vs the big corp. and not a horror movie that takes place in the wild with wildlife enthusiasts. we've seen a new corp try to take the dinosaurs and make their own "park" in JP 2 and I'm afraid that this is going to be too similar to JP 2. I, unlike most, quite like JP 2 but I don't want a JP 2-2.  I'm also not a fan of the humanization of the dinosaurs. They all act like humans or monsters. Idk. I'm looking forward to this movie, I see good and bad but I am worried. If they want to recapture the feel of a previous JP, they should imitate the first movie. Considering, however, that the first trailer looked a bit more like what I want than this one did, I have hopes that it will be good.

text: But why?¬†  Great effects, but practical effects would make it more believable... this makes it look unreal. Movies like this should be made with more practical effects, so that you won't have to stick giant filter over the entire film to make it look more scary and seem like it has awesome explosions. It is not believable.. colors are so "off" from the real world that it hurts.. and that is what ruins so many movies these days. When I don't get the feeling that this actually exists, it ceases to be scary. Colors shouldn't "pop" like that. It's like those horrible DC Comics movies, never learning from Marvel that to make a superhero believable.. the colors need to be right, more "true" to what you want the real world to be. I also still don't get why they have gone from terrifying dinosaurs that all wants you dead.. to, lets train them like pets and breed some mutant hybrid thingies to make the movie a bit more scary since people don't find tame things scary. It is like thinking "yeah, lets train tigers.. they will be completely tame, I promise... until they suddenly don't get enough food, or get bored with you one day, and eat you.. cause you are their pet as well".

text: This honestly looks like a better film than the first one. The first in this particular series, of course. No one will ever truly top the actual original film, but I really like this direction. It looks like they're going up instead of down or sideways, which exactly what we want in sequels. It harkens back to the good part of The Lost World where dinosaurs escape into the modern city and cause chaos, while also using the better atmosphere of the third film in the original trilogy that tried to be more horror-esque. Here's hoping it trims the fat and doesn't feel like the worse parts about those two awful films. Despite being a fan favorite, The Lost World was a complete mess filled with obnoxious plotholes, annoying characters and and a total lacking of the original spirit of the first film. The third film was just stupid despite a few interesting ideas, and if anything, felt more like a good episode of some TV show than a AAA movie.   Ultimately I really like what they look like they're doing here. It's an interesting setting and it looks like we've got some nice subplots that could lead to something.

text: I wish I had high expectations but I don't. The only two Jurassic Park movies I think were truly worthwhile were the originals, written by Crichton and then adapted for the silver screen. Both movies had compelling, realistic characters and plots that were action-packed and modestly thoughtful. The last few installments in the series have missed the "Might of Nature" motif and incorporated a gross amount of CGI and needless melodrama.   Definitely still going to watch Fallen Kingdom -- I'm just hoping, desperately, that the director and screenwriters can bring back the magic.
